Comment (src/components/ComplianceProgressPanel.vue:13):
**Low — permanently-zero "Inherited" tile in profile scope.**

Because `ProfileComplianceView` shares this panel without an `sspId` (and Contract A only populates `inherited` when `sspId` is present), this 6th tile reads "Inherited: 0" for every profile-scoped view, forever. The plan explicitly flagged this "for reviewer", so raising it for a decision rather than as a defect.

A one-liner hides it when it can't carry meaning:
```html
<div v-if="sspId || (summary.inherited ?? 0) > 0" class="rounded-lg border border-purple-200 bg-purple-50 p-4">
```
(and drop `md:grid-cols-6` back to `md:grid-cols-5` when the tile is absent, or keep 6 — cosmetic). Fine to leave as the accepted trade-off if you prefer; just calling the reviewer decision.
Replies:
**lisa implementation guidance:** Good call — taking the hide. The Inherited tile will render only when SSP-scoped (`sspId` set, where "Inherited: 0" is genuine information) or the count is > 0; the summary grid switches `md:grid-cols-6` ↔ `md:grid-cols-5` to match so there's no gap in profile scope. Recording this as the superseding decision over the earlier "accepted trade-off" note.

